dump until we're drowning in paperwork.

84
00:06:18,253 --> 00:06:23,382
All right.
We can deal with this. I mean, hey.

85
00:06:23,592 --> 00:06:27,928
It's... It's just paperwork. Right?

86
00:06:28,138 --> 00:06:31,515
- It's no big deal. Just hit it head on.
- Jimmy.

87
00:06:31,725 --> 00:06:34,351
Prioritise.
The most important stuff first.

88
00:06:34,561 --> 00:06:37,855
Or is it better to
deal with the easy stuff?

89
00:06:38,065 --> 00:06:40,649
You know, get that off the decks.

90
00:06:40,859 --> 00:06:44,528
You tell me, Chuck. You just
point to a box. We can do this.

91
00:06:44,738 --> 00:06:47,198
- Jimmy, we need to talk.
- Chuck.

92
00:06:47,407 --> 00:06:50,242
- Sit down, won't you?
- No, I'm good.

93
00:06:50,452 --> 00:06:52,870
I know you're not gonna
like what I have to say next.

94
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:54,538
But facts are facts.

95
00:06:54,748 --> 00:06:57,083
And what we're facing here...

96
00:06:57,292 --> 00:07:00,795
A case this size, it is not
a two man job. We need help.

97
00:07:01,004 --> 00:07:03,214
- No.
- And for the good of the clients...

98
00:07:03,423 --> 00:07:05,591
- ...we need to refer this case...
- Don't say it.

99
00:07:05,801 --> 00:07:07,551
Refer it out to HHM.

100
00:07:07,761 --> 00:07:11,222
Damn it, Chuck. No. Come on.

101
00:07:11,431 --> 00:07:16,268
We can do this.
We're doing great on our own.

102
00:07:16,478 --> 00:07:20,231
We don't need Hamlin or anyone else.
I mean, hey.

103
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:23,526
We can Erin Brockovich
the shit out of this case.

104
00:07:23,735 --> 00:07:25,903
Erin Brockovich didn't do it alone.

105
00:07:26,113 --> 00:07:28,114
She and Ed Masry
brought in heavy hitters...

106
00:07:28,323 --> 00:07:30,991
...from Los Angeles to get that
case across the goal line.

107
00:07:31,201 --> 00:07:34,995
And that's what we need to do.
And there's no shame in that.

108
00:07:35,205 --> 00:07:36,664
This is our case.

109
00:07:36,873 --> 00:07:40,459
Yes, it's ours.
And the task ahead is monumental.

110
00:07:40,669 --> 00:07:42,962
Could we do it alone?

111
00:07:43,672 --> 00:07:47,049
Could two men alone build
the Brooklyn Bridge? Maybe.

112
00:07:47,259 --> 00:07:49,468
But it would take forever.

113
00:07:49,678 --> 00:07:53,305
Just how long do you think the
residents of Sandpiper Crossing have?

114
00:07:54,182 --> 00:07:59,520
Referring this case to HHM
is for the good of the clients.

115
00:07:59,729 --> 00:08:03,107
That argument you won today
against the restraining order...

116
00:08:03,316 --> 00:08:05,234
...the judge was never
gonna grant that.

117
00:08:05,443 --> 00:08:07,736
Schweikart is throwing softballs.

118
00:08:07,946 --> 00:08:10,364
And he's gonna keep on
throwing them over and over.

119
00:08:10,574 --> 00:08:11,824
We'll be busy swatting them away...

120
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:14,076
...we'll never spend time
on the actual case.

121
00:08:14,286 --> 00:08:16,787
This case will span years.

122
00:08:16,997 --> 00:08:20,374
And we don't have the capital
to carry it forward by ourselves.

123
00:08:20,584 --> 00:08:22,585
We simply don't.

124
00:08:33,305 --> 00:08:35,931
- Fine.
- So?

125
00:08:36,641 --> 00:08:38,392
The case goes to HHM?

126
00:08:40,187 --> 00:08:43,898
Hail Satan. I submit to the dark side.

127
00:08:45,442 --> 00:08:47,902
I'll call Kim and arrange a meeting.

128
00:08:48,111 --> 00:08:51,488
All right. Good, Jimmy. Thank you.

129
00:08:51,698 --> 00:08:54,658
I know you'll come to see
that it's for the best.

130
00:09:07,047 --> 00:09:11,175
I guess I'll have to get
an office right next to yours.

131
00:09:13,011 --> 00:09:15,888
Finally out of the mailroom, huh?

132
00:10:47,272 --> 00:10:48,981
Yes. Hello.

133
00:10:49,941 --> 00:10:52,776
No. It's me.

134
00:11:27,645 --> 00:11:31,065
- This the place where we wait?
- Think so.

135
00:12:02,889 --> 00:12:04,473
So.

136
00:12:08,103 --> 00:12:10,646
What'd our guy tell you about the job?

137
00:12:12,816 --> 00:12:14,691
Not much.

138
00:12:16,486 --> 00:12:18,445
It's a protection job. Civilian.

139
00:12:19,864 --> 00:12:25,244
Guy is as green as they come, but we'll
be in there to make sure things fly right.

140
00:12:28,957 --> 00:12:32,418
You been doing this long?
I just assume we're all heavy hitters.

141
00:12:32,627 --> 00:12:33,669
And it makes sense.

142
00:12:33,878 --> 00:12:35,379
The vet recommends
the best of the best.

143
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:39,925
Dealing with some of these ethnic types,
blood tends to run a little hotter.

144
00:12:40,135 --> 00:12:43,554
That's just science. Physiology.

145
00:12:43,763 --> 00:12:47,433
There's historical precedent.
Know what I'm saying?

146
00:12:49,018 --> 00:12:51,937
So, what you packing?

147
00:12:53,273 --> 00:12:56,316
- A pimento.
- Sorry, what?

148
00:12:56,526 --> 00:12:58,735
Pimento sandwich.

149
00:13:00,155 --> 00:13:03,323
That's funny. Pimento.

150
00:13:05,118 --> 00:13:06,743
No, I mean, what are you carrying?

151
00:13:06,953 --> 00:13:09,121
You know, the piece?
What's the make?

152
00:13:09,330 --> 00:13:14,042
Pimento is a cheese.
They call it the caviar of the south.

153
00:13:14,252 --> 00:13:16,920
